# .repomixignore — strict exclusion list for `repomix` / `task repomix`.
#
# Repomix loads this automatically (gitignore syntax). Keep this file
# as the single source of truth for "what does NOT belong in an LLM
# bundle of this repo" — repomix.config.json carries only settings.
#
# Decision rule: if a file is generated, derived, or noise for a
# code-review LLM, exclude it. Source files always stay in.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Build outputs (already in .gitignore but listed for defense in depth)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
/target/
**/target/
**/target.cargo/
crates/crabcc-core/fuzz/target/
**/.crabcc/

# DMG / installer build artifacts (issue #107)
/dist/
/build/
**/dist/
**/web/dist/

# Repomix's own output (avoid double-packing)
/.repomix/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Lock + manifest detritus
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
**/*.lock
**/*-lock.json
package-lock.json
yarn.lock
pnpm-lock.yaml

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Generated docs + machine-generated specs
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# All markdown — narrative docs, CHANGELOG, ARCHITECTURE, RFCs. Source
# code carries enough rustdoc to explain itself, and bundling 350 KiB
# of prose drowns the actual logic.
**/*.md

# OpenAPI spec is generated/codegen'd from the MCP tool surface. Ship
# the source modules that build it, not the YAML output.
crates/crabcc-mcp/openapi.yaml
**/openapi.yaml
**/openapi.yml

# Other machine-generated artefacts
target/doc/
docs/build/
**/_book/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Static / binary resources — useless to a code-reviewing LLM
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
**/*.html
**/*.png
**/*.jpg
**/*.jpeg
**/*.gif
**/*.svg
**/*.icns
**/*.ico
**/*.woff
**/*.woff2
**/*.ttf
**/*.eot
**/*.pdf
**/*.zip
**/*.tar
**/*.tar.gz
**/*.tgz
**/*.dmg
**/*.gif
assets/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# macOS .app bundle scripts + plists (issue #107)
#
# These are install-time shell glue that ships inside Crabcc.app.
# They're code we author, but for an LLM debugging the *Rust crates*
# they're noise. Re-include explicitly via `--include` if you're
# auditing the installer surface specifically.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
installer/Crabcc.app/Contents/Resources/scripts/
installer/Crabcc.app/Contents/Resources/*.plist
installer/Crabcc.app/Contents/Info.plist

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Test fixtures + bench datasets — large by design, low signal per token
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
bench/
bench/results/
**/fixtures/
**/__fixtures__/
**/test-fixtures/
**/golden/
**/snapshots/
**/*.golden
**/snapshot.txt
**/*.snap

# Synthetic JSONL transcripts the memory-bench harness uses
crates/crabcc-memory-bench/data/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Per-developer scratch + summaries
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.summary/
.git/
.github/CODEOWNERS
.vscode/
.idea/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Misc
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
**/*.log
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db
